OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,FDr Remy Veness, co-lead author of the
OL,7,Fpaper from Sheffield Hallam
OL,8,FUniversity, said: "We recently
OL,9,Fdiscovered that the origin of the
OL,10,Faltar stone is north-east Scotland,
OL,11,Fbut how it travelled 700km to
OL,12,FSalisbury Plain is widely debated.
OL,14,F"Our research gives a new plausible
OL,15,Fexplanation for part of the journey to
OL,16,FSalisbury Plain.
OL,26,@pD@SOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,F"What is exciting about these findings
OL,7,Fis that they could imply that the
OL,8,Fpeople of Doggerland attached cultural
OL,9,Fsignificance to the altar stone long
OL,10,Fbefore it was incorporated into
OL,11,FStonehenge."
OL,13,FDoggerland, which once connected
OL,14,FBritain to mainland Europe, was
OL,15,Fabandoned due to climate change and is
OL,16,Fnow
OL,18,Fsubmerged under the North Sea.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,FDr Veness said the changing climate
OL,7,Fmay have been the reason for the
OL,8,F"audacious" decision to move the stone
OL,9,Fonto what is now mainland Britain.
OL,11,F"The altar stone must have been
OL,12,Fsignificant enough (for people) to be
OL,13,Fwilling to move the stone at least
OL,14,Ftwice," she said.
OL,16,F"First to save it from being submerged
OL,17,Fby rising sea levels at the end of the
OL,18,Flast ice age, and then again to its
OL,19,Ffinal resting place on Salisbury Plain.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@KO]sD@AOUvD@GO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,F"Moving the stone in response to
OL,7,Frising sea levels as the world's ice
OL,8,Fsheets melted at the end of the last
OL,9,Fice age goes some way to explaining
OL,10,Fwhy such an audacious move might have
OL,11,Fbeen attempted.
OL,13,F"It's really interesting to consider
OL,14,Fthat the construction of Stonehenge
OL,15,Fmight have started as a result of
OL,16,Fclimate-induced migration."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,FThe paper suggests that from
OL,7,FDoggerland, the altar stone could have
OL,8,Fbeen moved close to the Berkshire
OL,9,FRidgeway, the oldest road in Europe,
OL,10,Fwhich was active at the time of
OL,11,FStonehenge and could have eased or
OL,12,Fencouraged travel to Salisbury Plain.
OL,14,FCo-lead author Dr Anthony Clarke, from
OL,15,FCurtin University, said the findings
OL,16,Fsuggest the journey far from simple,
OL,17,Fand likely required careful planning
OL,18,Facross multiple stages.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,F"Rather than being carried naturally
OL,7,Fby ice, the evidence points to a
OL,8,Fdeliberate, carefully planned movement
OL,9,Facross a challenging and varied
OL,10,Flandscape," he said.
OL,12,F"Our modelling shows glaciers may have
OL,13,Ftransported rocks part of the way
OL,14,Fduring the last Ice Age ` potentially
OL,15,Fas far as Dogger Bank in the North Sea
OL,16,F` but not into southern England,
OL,17,Fmeaning the stone would still have
OL,18,Fneeded to be moved hundreds of
OL,19,Fkilometres by people.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@KO]tD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,F"The research indicates there were no
OL,7,Fviable glacial pathways linking the
OL,8,Fsource region directly to Stonehenge,
OL,9,Freinforcing the conclusion that human
OL,10,Ftransport was required.
OL,12,F"Instead, this suggests the stone was
OL,13,Flikely moved in stages, potentially
OL,14,Fcombining overland hauling with river
OL,15,For coastal transport where possible."
OL,17,FHe said the findings reveal a level of
OL,18,Forganisation and co-operation among
OL,19,FNeolithic communities not previously
OL,20,Ffully appreciated.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@eO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780589464
OL,3,CStonehenge mystery: Altar stone moved
OL,4,Cby glacier and ancient rescue mission
OL,6,F"Transporting a stone of this size
OL,7,Fover such a long distance would have
OL,8,Frequired planning, co-ordination and a
OL,9,Fdeep understanding of the landscape `
OL,10,Fnot to mention tremendous
OL,11,Fdetermination," he said.
OL,13,F"The study demonstrates how combining
OL,14,Fgeological analysis with computer
OL,15,Fmodelling can help resolve long-
OL,16,Fstanding questions about how
OL,17,FStonehenge was built."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@OO]uD@AOUyD@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/11
